  <p>
    Below is a summary of your Access Control Lists as Liquid Dragon
    knows them.  ACLs are based upon AFS PTS groups.  These ACLs give you
    access to departments.  A department has several permissions associated
    with it, such as a Web-Kickstart directory in AFS and RHN access.
  </p>

  <div py:if="message != ''" class="message">
    <p py:content="message"/>
  </div>

  <h2>Authorization Information</h2>

  <p>Greetings, ${fullname}.  You are user "${userid}".</p>

  <p>You are a member of the following ACL groups:</p>
  <ul py:if="len(acls) > 0">
    <li py:for="acl in acls" py:content="acl"/>
  </ul>
  <p py:if="len(acls) == 0">
    You have no ACL memberships.
  </p>

